  <exercises xml:id="hmwk-29">
    
    <exercise>
      <introduction>
        <p>
          Some students say that you can find the slope from a table by dividing the value of <m>y</m> by the value of <m>x</m> for a single data point.
        </p>
      </introduction>

      <task>
        <statement>
          <p>
            Does this method ever work? If so, for what types of functions will this method work? Give at least one example. Why does the method work?
          </p>
        </statement>
      </task>

      <task>
        <statement>
          <p>
            Try this method for finding slope on the function below. Does the method work? Why or why not? Is the data below linear? How do you know?
          </p>
          <tabular halign="center" top="minor" left="minor">
            <col header="yes" />
            <col/>
            <col/>
            <col/>
            <col/>
            <col/>
            <col/>
            <col/>
            <row bottom="minor">
              <cell right="minor"><m>x</m></cell>
              <cell right="minor">4</cell>
              <cell right="minor">6</cell>
              <cell right="minor">8</cell>
              <cell right="minor">10</cell>
              <cell right="minor">12</cell>
              <cell right="minor">14</cell>
              <cell right="minor">26</cell>
            </row>

            <row bottom="minor">
              <cell right="minor"><m>y</m></cell>
              <cell right="minor">7</cell>
              <cell right="minor">11</cell>
              <cell right="minor">15</cell>
